params.amount: amount of tokens user wants to buy from specific order

params.buy_amt: is the amount of the token user wants to buy
params.buy_gem: is an ERC20 token user wants to buy
params.max_fill_amount: The most amount that the caller is willing to pay. If slippage happens and price increases the user might end up with paying more of the pay_gem. In order to avoid big losses the caller should provide this threshold.
params.pay_gem: is an ERC20 token user wants to sell

params.buy_amt: is the amount of the token maker wants to buy
params.buy_gem: is an ERC20 token maker wants to buy
params.pay_amt: is the amount of the token maker wants to sell
params.pay_gem: is an ERC20 token maker wants to sell
params.pos: position where to insert the new offer, 0 should be used if unknown

params.buy_amt: is the amount of the token maker wants to buy
params.buy_gem: is an ERC20 token maker wants to buy
params.pay_amt: is the amount of the token maker wants to sell
params.pay_gem: is an ERC20 token maker wants to sell
params.pos: is the OFFER ID of the first offer that has a higher (or lower depending on whether it is bid or ask ) price than the new offer that the caller is making. 0 should be used if unknown.
params.rounding: boolean value indicating whether "close enough" orders should be matched

pause().details: Can be only called by HordCongress

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

params.buy_gem: is an ERC20 token user wants to buy
params.min_fill_amount: The least amount that the caller is willing to receive. If slippage happens and price declines the user might end up with less of the buy_gem. In order to avoid big losses the caller should provide this threshold
params.pay_amt: is the amount of the token user wants to sell
params.pay_gem: is an ERC20 token user wants to sell

params.maxTakeAmount: maximal amount of tokens user wants to buy from specific order

unpause().details: Can be only called by HordCongress

buy(uint256,uint256).notice: function that transfers funds from caller to offer maker, and from market to caller

buyAllAmount(address,uint256,address,uin.notice: function that attempts to exchange at most specified amount of pay_gem tokens for a specified amount of buy_gem tokens. It is possible that less tokens will be spent (depending on the current state of the orderbook). Transaction will fail if the method call determines that the caller will pay more than the amount specified as max_fill_amount.

cancel(uint256).notice: function that cancels an offer and refunds offer to maker

getOffer(uint256).notice: function that returns from specific order the buy token, buy token amount, sell token and sell token amount

getOwner(uint256).notice: function that returns owner address of specific order

isActive(uint256).notice: function that returns if offer is valid active offer

kill(bytes32).notice: function to kill specific order. Calls cancel function which executes the cancellation of the specific order

offer(uint256,address,uint256,address,ui.notice: function to make a new offer. Takes funds from the caller into market escrow

offerWithRounding(uint256,address,uint25.notice: function to make a new offer. Takes funds from the caller into market escrow

pause().notice: Function allowing congress to pause the smart-contract

sellAllAmount(address,uint256,address,ui.notice: function that attempts to exchange all of the pay_gem tokens for at least the specified amount of buy_gem tokens. It is possible that more tokens will be bought (depending on the current state of the orderbook). Transaction will fail if the method call determines that the caller will receive less amount than the amount specified as min_fill_amount.

take(bytes32,uint128).notice: function to take specific order. Calls buy function which executes the buy

unpause().notice: Function allowing congress to unpause the smart-contract
